      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DESCENDING MIST (4) tough gelding who appreciated the big class drop with a comprehensive victory over 2100m at Tamworth when shouldering the 60.5kg. Deep into the prep and will be strong late with the good early tempo. TOULON FACTOR (5) has a good record over this track and trip and will take catching with Small's 1.5kg claim. Cruised across from the wide gate when he led throughout to score over 1850m at Mudgee. Will handle the rise in grade and trip from the better gate. CENOTES (2) total forgive from the outside gate at his second run back with a plugging tenth over 1600m at Tamworth. Can race much closer here and the booking of Luke Rolls is a good lead. BONFIDELITY (6) proven at this trip and doesn't have to improve much to win this. Savaged the line when third over 1700m at Ipswich in C2 grade. Genuine winning prospect.",
